author: Andrew Jeong
title: North and South Korea Set Summit, but Nuclear Omission Casts a Shadow
text:
SEOUL—North and South Korea set a date for a meeting between leaders of the two countries, but failed to finalize an agenda for the summit, including whether the North’s nuclear program would be part of the talks.
The summit on April 27 would bring a North Korean leader to the South for the first time and be only the third meeting between leaders of the rival states.
